  "course_description": "Rotating topics in film and media across disciplines and crosslisted with other departments. May be repeated for credit when the topic varies.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as ITAL 276 1) MCP Elective An introduction to Italian media and the way that it functions as a cultural, creative, political, and economic force. Through lectures, social media analysis, media screenings, assigned readings, and weekly response papers, the course explores how Italian media reflects and magnifies broader issues of nationalism, race, gender, sexuality, and fandom. Each student will write responses, present a selected media example, follow and analyze an Italian social media influencer or series, and complete a final creative project. This class will be held in the Department of Film and Media's brand new production facility located at Emory Point. Address: 1568 Avenue Pl Ste 140 Atlanta, GA 30329",
